        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(media): suppress local whisper progress transcripts",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nLocal Whisper wrapper progress output no longer becomes the transcript when the wrapper produced no words. OpenClaw now treats the wrapper's expected `.txt` output as authoritative for the `local-whisper/transcribe.js` CLI path, while keeping stdout fallback behavior for other CLI transcription wrappers.\n\nThe fix covers `--output-dir`, `--output`, and `-o` output-directory forms. Empty or missing local-whisper transcript files now produce no transcript, and unexpected transcript-file read errors still surface instead of being hidden as silence.\n\nFixes openclaw/openclaw#87384.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `timeout -k5s 90s pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.media-understanding.config.ts src/media-understanding/runner.cli-audio.test.ts src/media-understanding/apply.test.ts --reporter verbose --testTimeout 10000`\n- `timeout -k5s 300s pnpm tsgo:core:test`\n- `git diff --check origin/main..HEAD`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode commit --commit HEAD --prompt 'Review the final media-understanding fix for issue #87384. Intent: local-whisper node wrappers that write transcript files should not fall back to progress stdout when the expected transcript file is empty or missing, including -o/--output/--output-dir forms; other CLI wrappers should preserve stdout fallback; unexpected transcript read errors should surface.'`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: local Whisper CLI wrapper status text could be injected as an audio transcript when the expected transcript file was empty or missing.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw source checkout on the PR branch `fix/local-whisper-cli-output`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: focused media-understanding Vitest coverage for `runner.cli-audio.test.ts` and `apply.test.ts`, plus `pnpm tsgo:core:test`.\n\nEvidence after fix: regression tests now cover non-empty local-whisper file output, empty file output, missing file output, `-o` output-dir spelling, stdout fallback for non-local node wrappers, and unexpected read errors.\n\nObserved result after fix: focused Vitest passed with 61 tests, `tsgo:core:test` exited 0, and autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nWhat was not tested: live Telegram/OpenClaw gateway transcription with a real audio attachment was not run for this upstream PR.\n\n## AI Assistance\n\nAI-assisted implementation and review. Local review included scoped simplify/code-review passes and the repo autoreview helper; findings were manually checked against the code before applying.\n\n---\n\n[![Compound Engineering](https://img.shields.io/badge/Built_with-Compound_Engineering-6366f1)](https://github.com/EveryInc/compound-engineering-plugin)\n![Codex](https://img.shields.io/badge/Codex-000000)\n",
